        <abstract> 
<p><hi rend="italic">Leucosmia burnettiana</hi> is in all probability dimorphic. Thinks <hi rend="italic">Gilia</hi> is truly heterostyled and <hi rend="italic">Phlox subulata</hi> was, perhaps, once heterostyled. Has good evidence of heterostyly in 39 genera from 14 families.</p> 
        </abstract>
